            <fr:title text="The way-below relation">The way-below relation</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:D]]></fr:tex> be two elements of a dcpo <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[D]]></fr:tex>; we say that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is <fr:em>way below</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y]]></fr:tex>, written <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\ll  y]]></fr:tex>, when for any directed subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I\subseteq  D]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y\sqsubseteq  \bigsqcup {I}]]></fr:tex>, there exists <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[z\in  I]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\sqsubseteq  z]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>(Adapted from <fr:link href="dejong-2023-thesis.xml" title="Domain theory in constructive and predicative univalent foundations" addr="dejong-2023-thesis" type="local">Tom de Jong’s thesis</fr:link>.)</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
